title: .docx word document parsing giving error

labels.name: wontfix
labels.description: This will not be worked on

body:
Firstly, I am new to fonduer and was trying to parse a word document using wiki president tutorial. I changed the parser to Doc_preprocessor  but it gave error "not implemented" . Probably because  the document object has nothing though I have placed the document at mentioned path. Do I need to provide HTML  for word docs as well?

code:

from fonduer.parser import Parser

docs_path = "data/contracts/"
doc_preprocessor = DocPreprocessor(docs_path)
doc_preprocessor

corpus_parser = Parser(session, structural=True, lingual=True)
